# Trust Architecture (Phase 19)

Read **[TRUST_ARCHITECTURE.md](../../TRUST_ARCHITECTURE.md)** before any feature touching customer data, permissions, connectors, learning, or audit.

## Core rule

**The customer owns the data. Aipify owns the intelligence layer.** If data is not required — do not collect, store, or process it.

## Layer placement

| Concern | Layer | Paths |
|---------|-------|-------|
| Governance & global audit metrics | Platform | `app/platform/trust/`, `get_platform_trust_governance` |
| Security Dashboard (transparency) | Customer | `app/app/settings/security/`, `components/app/trust/` |
| Installation/domain validation | Embedded | `lib/embed/validation.ts`, `lib/trust/installation.ts` |
| Shared rules | Shared | `lib/trust/` |

## Rules

1. Default access level: **metadata only** — higher levels require explicit approval
2. New integrations: **read-only first** — never auto-expand to write
3. Prohibited storage categories are blocked by default (`assertStorageAllowed`)
4. Metadata-first — store patterns/outcomes, not raw customer records
5. Sensitive operations → `record_trust_audit_event` (immutable log)
6. Privacy-by-design five questions — pause if answers unclear
7. New skills → `buildSkillSecurityReview()` before release
8. Global learning: anonymized metadata only — never identities or communications
9. Platform Admin must not browse customer operational data unnecessarily

> Aipify becomes trusted because of what it refuses to collect.
